Components structure:
    - src/components - folder with all custom components
    - Each component has own file or folder
    - CamelCase naming

Syntax:
    - <div></div>, <></> or <React.Fragment> as root tag - Component must have root tag for a return statement
    - return (...) - for multiple lines
    - className=”...” - define css class
    - props - makes component reusable
    - {} - run basic javascript expression
    - props.children
    - Transformation JSX to React.createElement

Events:
    Full access to native DOM events

    Classic way: document.getElementById("id").addEventListener('click', ()=>{...})
    React way: <button onClick={()=>{...}} />

    Recommendation: name should end with "handler"
      Ex.:
         const clickHandler = () => {...}
         <button onClick={clickHandler} />

List item key

